 We remain committed to delivering improved profitability and higher returns in 2020 and beyond. Returning value to our shareholders has been at the core of Union Bank’s transformation and continuous drive to become a leading financial institution in Nigeria. Notwithstanding the tough operating environment, we remain focused on our strategy and ambition as we strive towards achieving our ambition to be Nigeria’s most reliable and trusted banking partner” Other business conducted during the AGM included the election and re-election of Directors and members of the Statutory Audit Committee by the shareholders; the appointment of Messrs. Ernst and Young as the External Auditor; and the authorisation of the Directors to fix the remuneration of the Auditor.